    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-26T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-26T07:00:00-05:00" n="956"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d956">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/7–2649: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-26T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 26, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 26—1:42 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1628. In effort to seek concerted action on protests to Communist authorities
                    over lack of protection, miscarriage of justice in cases involving Americans,
                    Embassy requests Department’s opinion of following proposed circular telegram to
                    all posts in Communist China: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In all cases involving Americans in your district where clear evidence
                            exists lack protection afforded by Communist authorities, you are
                            instructed (1) attempt protest through most effective or feasible
                            channels to local authorities citing circumstances, (2) provide
                            Consulate General Peiping with details in order it may attempt lodge
                            similar protest with headquarters Communist authorities, (3) provide
                            same information to Nanking which will attempt protest as [an] Embassy,
                            (4) repeat information to Department.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
